I"v<p>While the L1, L2 norms, and p-norm in general are <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/optimizing-for-short-semantic-distances-fosters-learning">distance functions</a> which take into consideration the magnitude of the two <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/one-hot-encodings-are-basis-vectors-in-type-space">vectors</a> involved, cosine similarity only indicates how well the two vectors are aligned in space, regardless of their magnitude. Cosine similarity is the default choice in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/multi-lingual-embeddings-formalize-geography-of-thought">word embeddings</a>.</p>
